creator: tom@zeebit.com
text:
Well, after a clean install using default options, and not attempting to install
with any other modules i get this errror :

[Fri Aug 15 17:13:20 2003] [notice] Parent: Created child process 4968
[Fri Aug 15 17:13:21 2003] [notice] Child 4968: Child process is running
[Fri Aug 15 17:13:21 2003] [crit] (OS 10045)The attempted operation is not
supported for the type of object referenced.  : Parent: WSADuplicateSocket
failed for socket 2523824. Check the FAQ.
[Fri Aug 15 17:13:21 2003] [crit] (OS 10045)The attempted operation is not
supported for the type of object referenced.  : master_main: create child
process failed. Exiting.
[Fri Aug 15 17:13:21 2003] [crit] (OS 109)The pipe has been ended.  :
setup_inherited_listeners: Unable to read socket data from parent
[Fri Aug 15 17:13:21 2003] [notice] Parent: Forcing termination of child process
2539080 

Apache fails to start, and the program fails.

creator: stoddard@apache.org
text:
Did you consult the FAQ as the error message suggested?

Here is the particular entry:
http://httpd.apache.org/docs/misc/FAQ.html#WSADuplicateSocket
